A: The problem is that you're not sending newline characters (\n or \r\n) between your lines. The BufferedReader.readLine() method reads until it encounters a newline character, so it's reading the entire stream as one line.
You should add newline characters after each write:
printWriter.write("1\n");
printWriter.write("2\n");
printWriter.write("3\n");

Or, if you want to send multiple lines without newlines, you can use println() instead of write():
printWriter.println("1");
printWriter.println("2");
printWriter.println("3");

Then, when you read the lines, you should use readLine() in a loop until it returns null:
String line;
while ((line = bufferedReader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}

This will read each line separately.

